7. The use of study data
309 310
The data and conclusions derived from the PMCF study are used to provide
clinical
311
evidence for the clinical evaluation process. This may result in the
need to reassess
312
whether the device continues to comply with the Essential Requirements.
Such
313
assessment may result in corrective or preventive actions, for example
changes to the
314
labelling/instructions for use, changes to manufacturing processes,
changes to the
315
device design, or public health notifications.
