9.1. General considerations In order to determine the value of the data
identified in stage 1, the evaluators should appraise each individual
document in terms of its contribution to the evaluation of the clinical
performance and clinical safety of the device. Uncertainty arises from
two sources: the methodological quality of the data, and the relevance
of the data to the evaluation of the device in relation to the different
aspects12 of its intended purpose. Both sources of uncertainty should be
analysed to determine a weighting for each data set. The evaluators
should therefore:
